# Revlane Signal Engine — Technical Summary

## What It Does

A **LinkedIn lead qualification tool** that takes a list of LinkedIn profile URLs and determines which leads are worth pursuing. It runs a two-phase pipeline on each lead:

1. **Phase 1 — Activity Gate**: Checks if the person posted on LinkedIn within the last 60 days. Inactive leads are rejected immediately.
2. **Phase 2 — Contact Discovery**: For active leads, scrapes their first name, personal website(s), and email address(es) from LinkedIn's contact overlay and their personal website.

The result is a filtered, enriched list of qualified leads with contact information, exportable as CSV or directly to Google Sheets.

---

## Inputs

| Input | Format | Description |
|---|---|---|
| LinkedIn URLs | CSV file (single column) | Dropped or uploaded via the dashboard UI |
| Processing limit | Number | Controls how many leads from the CSV to process |

## Outputs

| Output | Format | Description |
|---|---|---|
| Qualified leads table | In-app UI | Real-time status per lead: first name, activity status, websites, emails, per-lead logs |
| CSV export | `.csv` download | LinkedIn URL, first name, status, activity status, websites, emails |
| Google Sheets export | Google Spreadsheet | Same data, formatted and styled in a new or existing Google Sheet |
| Progress saves | JSON files in `progress/` | Auto-saved on every lead for crash recovery; loadable run history |

---

## Architecture & Lead Pipeline

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A["CSV Upload (Dashboard)"] --> B["processSingleLead()"]
    B --> C{"Phase 1: Activity Gate"}
    C -->|"Active (≤60 days)"| D["Phase 2: Contact Discovery"]
    C -->|"Inactive"| E["REJECTED"]
    C -->|"API fail/timeout (5 retries)"| F["ACTIVITY_FAILED"]
    D --> G["fetchProfileContactInfo()"]
    G --> H["Parse contact overlay HTML"]
    H --> I{"Has personal website?"}
    I -->|Yes| J["discoverDeepWeb() — crawl for emails"]
    I -->|No| K["Done"]
    J --> K
    K --> L["QUALIFIED"]
    F -->|"Retry Failed button"| M["retrySingleLead() — skip Phase 1"]
    M --> D
```

### Phase 1 — [gateLeadActivity()](file:///c:/Users/mimod/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/leads_qualiferV2/src/app/actions/scraper-actions.ts#329-518)
- Calls **Bright Data's Dataset API** (`BD_DATASET_ACTIVITY`) with the LinkedIn URL and a 90-day date window
- Polls for results via [pollBrightData()](file:///c:/Users/mimod/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/leads_qualiferV2/src/app/actions/scraper-actions.ts#1399-1428) if a snapshot ID is returned
- Parses date fields (`date_posted`, [date](file:///c:/Users/mimod/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/leads_qualiferV2/src/lib/env.ts#23-54), `created_at`, etc.) to find most recent post
- Lead is **Active** if latest post is ≤ 60 days old, **Inactive** otherwise
- `dead_page` error code → definitively inactive
- Up to **5 outer attempts** × **2 inner retries** with 10s/5s delays + a 120s hard timeout

### Phase 2 — [discoverLeadData()](file:///c:/Users/mimod/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/leads_qualiferV2/src/app/actions/scraper-actions.ts#519-609) → [fetchProfileContactInfo()](file:///c:/Users/mimod/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/leads_qualiferV2/src/app/actions/scraper-actions.ts#610-829)
- Authenticates to LinkedIn using the `li_at` session cookie
- **Step 1**: Visits the profile page to pick up session cookies + extract `<title>` for first name
- **Step 2**: Fetches `/in/{slug}/overlay/contact-info/` for websites and emails
- Parses the overlay HTML via [parseOverlayHtml()](file:///c:/Users/mimod/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/leads_qualiferV2/src/app/actions/scraper-actions.ts#830-953) (LinkedIn redirect URLs, embedded JSON, raw regex)
- Decodes Cloudflare-obfuscated emails when encountered
- Falls back to URL slug for first name (hyphenated split or camelCase detection)

### Deep Web Crawl — [discoverDeepWeb()](file:///c:/Users/mimod/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/leads_qualiferV2/src/app/actions/scraper-actions.ts#1088-1196)
- Takes the first non-LinkedIn website found on the profile
- Fetches that homepage via [fetchPage()](file:///c:/Users/mimod/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/leads_qualiferV2/src/app/actions/scraper-actions.ts#1314-1398) (raw HTTPS with timeout)
- Discovers internal links (contact, about, team pages) via [discoverInternalLinks()](file:///c:/Users/mimod/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/leads_qualiferV2/src/app/actions/scraper-actions.ts#1197-1252)
- Crawls up to 5 internal pages looking for email addresses
- All emails pass through [validateEmail()](file:///c:/Users/mimod/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/leads_qualiferV2/src/lib/utils.ts#25-60) + [isPlaceholderEmail()](file:///c:/Users/mimod/OneDrive/Desktop/Projects/leads_qualiferV2/src/app/actions/scraper-actions.ts#1280-1313) filters

